article.headline: N. Illinois 81, Ohio 74
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio (AP) -- Cody Yelder scored 20 points and made four free throws in the closing seconds Saturday, helping Northern Illinois hold on for an 81-74 victory over Ohio. Northern Illinois (6-17, 3-8 Mid-American) used a balanced attack and accurate shooting in the second half. The Huskies went 14-of-20 from the field in the second half, building their lead to 12 points. Ryan Paradise scored 18 points, and Shaun Logan added 17 for Northern Illinois. Ohio (16-8, 7-4) wore throwback jerseys modeled after its 1960s uniforms, part of a celebration of the Bobcats' 100th basketball season. The Bobcats struggled through poor 3-point shooting, going only 6-of-27 from behind the arc. Leon Williams scored 18 points, leading four Ohio players in double figures. Bubba Walther was 2-of-11 on 3-point shots, finishing with nine points. Shaun Logan scored 16 points in the first half for Northern Illinois, which led 36-32 at the break. Mike McKinney's layup made it 64-52 with 3:40 left in the game, the Huskies' biggest lead. Layups by Whitney Davis and Sonny Troutman cut it to 77-74 with 26 seconds left. Yelder was fouled and made both free throws, blunting the comeback. After Troutman missed a 3-point shot, Yelder got the rebound, was fouled and made two more free throws with 12 seconds left.
